'''Ricardo Adé Kat''' (born 21 May 1990) is a [[Haiti]]an professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (football)|defender]] for Ecuadorian club [[L.D.U. Quito]] and the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Career==
Adé intended to play in [[Thailand]] but he was victim of a fraud when the agent abandoned him while in Thailand.<ref name="primicias">{{cite web |last1=Cordoba |first1=Martha |title=Ricardo Adé, de dormir en las calles de Tailandia a ser figura en Liga |url=https://www.primicias.ec/noticias/jugada/eldeportequequeremos/ricardo-ade-haiti-liga-quito/ |website=Primicias |access-date=1 June 2023}}</ref> Since he couldn't play in Thailand, Adé moved to the [[United States]] and started playing for [[Miami United]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cordova |first=Martha |date=14 May 2023 |title=Ricardo Adé, de dormir en las calles de Tailandia a ser figura en Liga |url=https://www.primicias.ec/noticias/jugada/eldeportequequeremos/ricardo-ade-haiti-liga-quito/ |url-status=bot: unknown |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230601213924/https://www.primicias.ec/noticias/jugada/eldeportequequeremos/ricardo-ade-haiti-liga-quito/ |access-date=15 November 2023 |website=Primicias |archive-date=1 June 2023 }}</ref><ref name="NFT">{{NFT player|id=65026|accessdate=}}</ref>

In 2017, Adé went to [[Santiago Morning]]. In his first season, he played 23 matches and scored 1 goal.<ref name="gráfico">{{cite news|last1=Ríos|first1=Javier|title=Ricardo Adé, el héroe de los haitianos que sueña con triunfar en el fútbol chileno|trans-title=Ricardo Adé, the haitian hero who dreams on succeeding in Chilean football.|url=https://www.publimetro.cl/cl/grafico-chile/2017/11/08/ricardo-ade-el-primer-jugador-haitiano-en-chile.html|accessdate=11 February 2018|agency=Publimetro Chile|publisher=El Gráfico Chile|date=8 November 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref> An agent sent the videos of Adé playing for Miami United to the president of [[Primera B de Chile]] club [[Deportes Magallanes|Magallanes]] and the club hired Adé.<ref name=primicias/> After 4 years in Chile, Adé had the opportunity to play at [[Ecuadorian Serie A|First Division level in Ecuador]], when he signed with [[Mushuc Runa S.C.]] in 2021.<ref name=primicias/> A year later, Adé was crowned as champions of [[2022 Ecuadorian Serie A]] with [[S.D. Aucas]].<ref name=primicias/> In 2023, Adé became a top player in Ecuador playing for [[L.D.U. Quito]].<ref name=primicias/>

Adé made his international debut for [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] in 2016.<ref name = "NFT"/> He became captain in 2021.<ref name=primicias/>

